  ## The Daily Time Blocks (Template)

  <p className="mb-4 text-gray-700">
    Use these time blocks to structure your most productive 4-hour window (e.g., 9:00–13:00).
  </p>

  <ul className="list-disc pl-5 space-y-3">
    <li><strong>Focus (90m):</strong> Deep, high-leverage work toward Top 3 outcomes. Zero distractions.</li>
    <li><strong>Admin (45m):</strong> Email, quick comms, expenses. Batch here.</li>
    <li><strong>People (45m):</strong> Meetings, calls, coaching, check-ins.</li>
    <li><strong>Buffer (30m):</strong> Rest, transitions, fires, or prep.</li>
  </ul>

  <Note tone="key" title="Rule of 3" className="mt-8">
    Start every Monday by writing down your <strong>Top 3 Outcomes</strong> for the week. If you hit those 3, the week was a success.
  </Note>

